---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Now";
const description = "What I'm up to currently";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="space-y-8">
    <header class="space-y-2 md:px-2">
      <h1 class="text-2xl text-foreground sm:text-3xl">{title}</h1>
      <p class="max-w-[60ch] text-pretty text-foreground-muted">{description}</p>
    </header>
    <main class="space-y-6 md:px-2">
      <article class="now-card">
        <header class="now-head flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4">
          <span class="small-heading">Now</span>
          <time datetime="2026-02-02" class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground-muted"
            >February 2, 2026</time
          >
        </header>
        <div class="now-body">
          <p>
            I just returned from my first company offsite which took place in
            Portland, OR. It was a long week but great to meet everyone in-person
            and get to know everyone better.
          </p>
          <p>
            During February, I plan to continue my focus on my mental and
            physical health including returning to the gym which I'm excited for.
            I'm also focusing a lot on my finances this year to prepare to move
            into a new apartment next year. The plans are made, now it's up to me
            to execute.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'm also excited for a handful of projects I'm working on, one of
            which is a personal dashbaord I can use to track various things like
            my social following, habits, to-dos, and more. Think of it like a
            one-stop-shop for myself.
          </p>
          <p>
            More on that will be shared in the near-ish future on my <a
              href="https://x.com/ryandotfurrer">X/Twitter</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>
        <dl class="now-meta">
          <div class="now-row flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
            <dt class="small-heading shrink-0 sm:w-28">Watching</dt>
            <dd class="flex-1 text-pretty">
              Finishing up <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uXr9Ha9qRHE"
                >Dan Da Dan (Season 2)</a
              >, then rewatching <a
                href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Iwr1aLEDpe4"
                >Frieren: Beyond Journey's End, Season 1</a
              > before diving into <a
                href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EOMVXqH9DSg">Season 2</a
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="now-row flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
            <dt class="small-heading shrink-0 sm:w-28">Reading</dt>
            <dd class="flex-1 text-pretty">
              Finishing up <a
                href="https://store.dailystoic.com/collections/all-books/products/the-obstacle-is-the-way-expanded-10th-anniversary-edition"
                >The Obstacle is the Way by Ryan Holiday</a
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="now-row flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
            <dt class="small-heading shrink-0 sm:w-28">Playing</dt>
            <dd class="flex-1 text-pretty">
              <a href="https://www.expedition33.com/"
                >Clair Obscur: Expedition 33</a
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="now-row flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
            <dt class="small-heading shrink-0 sm:w-28">Obsessed with</dt>
            <dd class="flex-1 text-pretty">
              This cover of <a href="https://youtu.be/KsrN_jsDFOA?si=dRT_Mg1ffS_CYfIG"
                >Radiohead's "Creep" by Erin Morton</a
              > and a cover of <a
                href="https://youtu.be/9WoCqEZMBL0?si=Olk9GyCHzv2VywOW"
                >"New York, New York" by Lawrence</a
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </article>
      <article class="now-card">
        <header class="now-head flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4">
          <span class="small-heading">Previously</span>
          <time datetime="2026-01-01" class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground-muted"
            >January 1, 2026</time
          >
        </header>
        <div class="now-body">
          <p>
            Focusing on both my mental and physical health, giving it all at my
            job, and moving into a new apartment next year. I'm setting up the
            systems now to help me stay on track and meet my goals.
          </p>
        </div>
        <dl class="now-meta">
          <div class="now-row flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
            <dt class="small-heading shrink-0 sm:w-28">Watching</dt>
            <dd class="flex-1 text-pretty">
              <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uXr9Ha9qRHE"
                >Dan Da Dan (Season 2)</a
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="now-row flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
            <dt class="small-heading shrink-0 sm:w-28">Reading</dt>
            <dd class="flex-1 text-pretty">
              <a
                href="https://store.dailystoic.com/collections/all-books/products/the-obstacle-is-the-way-expanded-10th-anniversary-edition"
                >The Obstacle is the Way by Ryan Holiday</a
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="now-row flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
            <dt class="small-heading shrink-0 sm:w-28">Playing</dt>
            <dd class="flex-1 text-pretty">
              <a href="https://www.expedition33.com/"
                >Clair Obscur: Expedition 33</a
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="now-row flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
            <dt class="small-heading shrink-0 sm:w-28">Obsessed with</dt>
            <dd class="flex-1 text-pretty">
              <a
                href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jH3xpS7Q_3E&list=OLAK5uy_k_hE5HhMiwlHuzdS7R17Yk8w68ilnSrMw&index=2"
                >Final Fantasy VII Remake Acoustic Arrangements</a
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </article>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Ruled-notebook "journal page" cards.
     Everything sits on one baseline grid: every line-height and every vertical
     gap is a multiple of --r, and the horizontal rules repeat every --r at the
     text baseline (--baseline), so the writing lands ON the lines. Bright-white
     paper is defined by the hairline + soft shadow + rules; a faint left margin
     rule (tied to the accent) runs down the side. */
  .now-card {
    --r: 1.75rem; /* the single rhythm unit */
    --baseline: 1.32rem; /* where the rule sits within a line (≈ text baseline) */
    line-height: var(--r);
    padding: var(--r) 1.5rem var(--r) 3rem;
    background-color: oklch(0.999 0 0);
    /* A single tiled rule line (via background-size/-repeat) rather than
       repeating-linear-gradient — WebKit drops thin repeating bands partway
       down a tall element, so the lines would stop rendering in Safari. */
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(
        to right,
        transparent 0 2.25rem,
        color-mix(in oklch, var(--link) 35%, transparent) 2.25rem 2.28rem,
        transparent 2.28rem
      ),
      linear-gradient(to bottom, oklch(0.45 0.12 250 / 0.13) 0 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size:
      100% 100%,
      100% var(--r);
    background-repeat:
      no-repeat,
      repeat;
    background-position:
      0 0,
      0 var(--baseline);
    border: 1px solid oklch(0 0 0 / 0.07);
    border-radius: 0.6rem;
    box-shadow:
      0 1px 2px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.05),
      0 12px 32px -18px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.18);
  }

  /* Lock every line to the rhythm. */
  .now-card :is(p, dt, dd, span, time, a) {
    line-height: var(--r);
  }

  /* All vertical spacing is a whole number of rule lines so nothing drifts. */
  .now-card > * + *,
  .now-body > * + * {
    margin-top: var(--r);
  }
  .now-row + .now-row {
    margin-top: 0; /* rows flow line-by-line, like list entries on the page */
  }

  /* Inside the cards the "writing" reads as a single ink color: body copy and
     its values use the foreground, and links drop the accent — the underline
     alone marks them. (Eyebrow, date, and category labels keep their styling.) */
  .now-body,
  .now-row dd {
    color: var(--color-foreground);
  }
  .now-card :is(.now-body, .now-row dd) a {
    color: var(--color-foreground);
    text-decoration-color: color-mix(
      in oklch,
      var(--color-foreground) 40%,
      transparent
    );
  }
  .now-card :is(.now-body, .now-row dd) a:hover {
    color: var(--color-foreground);
    text-decoration-color: currentColor;
  }

  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    .now-card {
      background-color: oklch(0.21 0 0);
      background-image:
        linear-gradient(
          to right,
          transparent 0 2.25rem,
          color-mix(in oklch, var(--link) 42%, transparent) 2.25rem 2.28rem,
          transparent 2.28rem
        ),
        linear-gradient(to bottom, oklch(0.92 0 0 / 0.07) 0 1px, transparent 1px);
      border-color: oklch(1 0 0 / 0.08);
      box-shadow: none;
    }
  }
</style>
